Im sorry to all of my friends that i have not talk to in the last few weeks. Especially britt. Ive been exteremly busy with lots of stuff. 4 or 5 projects, band practice, driving, math, getting ready for my bands show. And my mom is going a bit crazy, and thats no joke. Shes still sane, but she freaks out really easily now. She been taking medication for years and now shes trying to get off of it so thats the cause. When she freaks out then she takes my computer, which means i cant talk to some of you. And im sorry. I miss you and ive been getting comments on myspace about how we havent talked in a while. Im sorry. And im sorry to britt, i havent talked to you in 5 days:(. I have been so fucking busy, my day after school is always so full of stuff i never have a chance for anything anymore. But now that i only have 2 projects instead of 5 hopefully things will change. I love you and if you think im forgetting about you, dont ever think that, because i never will. So new resolution for this week! Talk to more people on msn!!!

I love you all


Anyways my band had our first show last night:D:D:D:D:D
It was amazing and i will never ever forget it. We had to wake up at 6 to go to sound check which sucked, and it wasnt much of a soundcheck haha but it was fun. then we went home practiced for a long time. We just got a new bass player, hes temporary though, so we had to teach him all the shit in two practices haha. Hes really good though so he got it easily. Then we got to slims(the venue) at 4 30, put our stuff down, watched some of the other bands, who sucked ass. THen played at 6:D
And we got the crowed so pumped up! it was amazing. Everyone was moshing some people were dancing:D:D:D:D. Id rather have more dancing haha but its all good. Our guitarist said it well when he said, "We represented all the hardcore and metal kids there" It was such a great feeling to do something like that. All the other bands were really shitty emo/indie. And not the good kind. I like that kind of music but they just sucked. The crowd did absolutly nothing to them, and when we got on they went crazy. I loved it and i want to do this for the rest of my life. All the energy we brought on stage was so crazy. I loved it, we messed up a few times and it was because our drummer dropped his stick haha but we fixed it. I love doing this.
O yeah and if you think i sound like an asshole for saying the other bands sucked im sorry. If you heard them you would probably agree. Although the band who played after us were pretty good, they were an all girl band, and were talented. The singer was kinda annoying but they were good.
Anyways now that all thats done,im gonna go do some of my fucking projects   :( britt i call you once you get home ok? I love you
Bye everyone
